errorDescription.400: There is a syntax error in the request, and it is denied.
errorDescription.401: The request header did not contain the necessary authentication codes, and the client is denied access.
errorDescription.403: The client is not allowed to see a certain file. This is also returned at times when the server doesn't want any more visitors.
errorDescription.404: The requested file was not found on the server. Possibly because it was deleted, or never existed before. Often caused by misspellings of URLs.
errorDescription.405: The method you are using to access the file is not allowed.
errorDescription.406: The requested file exists but cannot be used as the client system doesn't understand the format the file is configured for.
errorDescription.407: The request must be authorised before it can take place.
errorDescription.408: The server took longer than its allowed time to process the request. Often caused by heavy net traffic.
errorDescription.409: Too many concurrent requests for a single file.
errorDescription.410: The file used to be in this position, but is there no longer.
errorDescription.411: The request is missing its Content-Length header.
errorDescription.412: A certain configuration is required for this file to be delivered, but the client has not set this up.
errorDescription.413: The requested file was too big to process.
errorDescription.414: The address you entered was overly long for the server.
errorDescription.415: The filetype of the request is unsupported.
errorDescription.500: Server is confused, often caused by an error in the server-side program responding to the request.
errorDescription.501: The request cannot be carried out by the server.
errorDescription.503: The service or file that is being requested is not currently available.
